{"lemma":"رَبٌّ","slug":"رَبٌّ","root":"ر.ب.ب","root_slug":"ر-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَبّ","root":"ربب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":975},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["adj","adv","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14368"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be master, to be lord"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have possession, to gather, to control"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have authority over, to govern"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to impact, to comprise, to contain"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to collect, to congregate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grow, to increase, to become greater"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bring up, to raise (a child)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"master, lord, king, sovereign, potentate","examples":[{"text":"رَبُّ الدَّار","english":"master of the house"},{"text":"رَبُّ الْعَائِلَة","english":"paterfamilias"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Lord, an epithet of God","examples":[{"text":"اَللهُ رَبُّ الْعَالَمِين","english":"God is Lord of the Worlds"},{"text":"الرَّبّ","english":"the LORD"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"god, deity","examples":[{"text":"يَا صَاحِبَيِ السِّجْنِ أَأَرْبَابٌ مُّتَفَرِّقُونَ خَيْرٌ أَمِ اللّٰهُ الْوَاحِدُ الْقَهَّارُ","english":"[Joseph said:] \"O my two companions of the prison! Are many different deities better than God the One [Who is the Source of all things], the Overpowering?\""}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"leader, chief, head","examples":[{"text":"رَبُّ بَحْرِيّ","english":"seaman (naval rank)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"owner, proprietor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one possessed of, one endowed with"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"having to do with"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَبَّ (rabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thickened fruit juice, thickened juice"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mash, pulp"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"many","examples":[{"text":"رُبَّ رَجُلٍ","english":"many a man"},{"text":"رُبَّ مَرَّةٍ","english":"many a time"}]},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"likely, perhaps, mayhap, potentially"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *rabb-."},"ipa":["/rab.ba/","/rabb/","/rubb/","/rub.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14368","headword_ar":"رَبٌّ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lord, a possessor, an owner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a proprietor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlikN","text_ar":"مَالِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, IAmb, S, M, A, Msb, K,) of a thing, (T,) of anything, (S, M, A, K,) or of an irrational thing; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person who has a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"just title"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"claim, to the possession"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything; or its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHib","text_ar":"صَاحِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlik","text_ar":"مَالِك"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, A, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlikN","text_ar":"مَالِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibN","text_ar":"صَاحِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"all signifying in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xudaAwanod","text_ar":"خُدَاوَنْد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (KL:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lord, master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lord, master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief, to whom obedience is paid:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lord, ruler, governor, regulator,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an orderer, a rectifier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reformer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rearer, fosterer, bringer-up, feeder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nourisher:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a completer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an accomplisher:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) it is an epithet, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nam~N","text_ar":"نَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nam~a","text_ar":"نَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or an inf. n. used as an intensive epithet; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ksh and Bd * in i. l;) originally signifying the “ bringing (a thing) to a state of completion by degrees;” (Bd, ibid.;) then used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlikN","text_ar":"مَالِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ksh and Bd ibid.:) the pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaAbN","text_ar":"اَرْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuwbN","text_ar":"رُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and accord. to Sh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbN","text_ar":"رِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, (TA,) signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbN","text_ar":"اَصْحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabuwbN","text_ar":"رَبُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is app. a quasi-pl. n.: (M:) the fem. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~apN","text_ar":"رَبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~aAtN","text_ar":"رَبَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) Whoever possesses a thing is its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~","text_ar":"رَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa rab~u Ald~aAb~api","text_ar":"هُوَ رَبُّ الدَّابَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the possessor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"owner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master, of the beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAri","text_ar":"الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the house"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (T,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAli","text_ar":"المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayoti","text_ar":"البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa rab~apu","text_ar":"هِىَ رَبَّةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is the owner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mistress, of the house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) With the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is [properly] applied only to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, Msb, K:) He is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~u AlA^arobaAbi","text_ar":"رَبُّ الاَرْبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Lord of lords"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T. [Thus the pl. with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to created beings.]) To any other being it is not [properly] applied but as a prefixed noun governing another noun as its complement in the gen. case [or in a similar manner]. (S.) The pagan Arabs, however, sometimes applied it to A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"king,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or to a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) El- Hárith says, (S, Msb,) i. e. Ibn-Hillizeh, (S,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wahuwa Alr~ab~u waAl$~ahiydu EalaY yuwo\n                      \n                     \n                        mi AlHiyaArayoni waAlbalaA='u balaA='u"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning El-Mundhir Ibn-Má-es-Semà, or, as some say, 'Amr Ibn-Hind,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was the king"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and witness of"},{"kind":"text","text":"our fighting on"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the day of El-Hiyárán"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the name of a place),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the trial was a"},{"kind":"text","text":"hard"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trial."},{"kind":"text","text":"(EM, p. 285: [in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayaArayoni","text_ar":"الحَيَارَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHiyaArayoni","text_ar":"الحِيَارَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Some forbid that a man should be called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~","text_ar":"رَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of his slave: (Msb:) it is said in a trad. that the slave shall not say to his master,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~Y","text_ar":"رَبّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it is like attributing a partner to God: (TA:) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~","text_ar":"رَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used in the sense of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to a noun signifying a rational being governed by it in the gen. case: thus in the saying of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY talida AlA^amapu rab~ahaA","text_ar":"حَتَّى تَلِدَ الاَمَةُ رَبَّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"So that the female slave shall bring forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"him who will become"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her master"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~atahaA","text_ar":"رَبَّتَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her mistress"},{"kind":"text","text":"], accord. to different transmitters; (Msb;) relating to the signs of the hour of resurrection: i. e., the female slave shall bring forth to her master a child that shall be as a master [or mistress] to her because like his [or her] father in rank: meaning that captives and concubines shall be numerous. (TA.) As to the phrase in the Kur [xii. 42],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Au*okuroniY Einoda rab~ika","text_ar":"اُذْكُرْنِى عِنْدَ رَبِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mention thou me in the presence of thy lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"], Joseph thus addressed his fellow-prisoner agreeably with the acceptation in which he [the latter] understood the words. (TA.) A similar instance also occurs in the same chapter, in the verse immediately preceding. (Msb.) In another verse, [23 of the same ch.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu rab~iY","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ رَبِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is my lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"] may refer to Joseph's master or to God. (M, TA.) The words of the Kur [lxxxix. 28 and 29],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirojiEiY A_ilaY rab~iki raADiyapF","text_ar":"اِرْجِعِى اـِلَى رَبِّكِ رَاضِيَةً"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroDiy~apF faA@doxuliY fiY EabodYi","text_ar":"مَرْضِيَّةً فَا@دْخُلِى فِى عَبْدىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as some read, [instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAdiY","text_ar":"عِبَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Return to thine owner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approving, approved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and enter into my servant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) ―         -b2-  Without the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", as some say, (L, TA,) it is sometimes written and pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabN","text_ar":"رَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", without teshdeed; (L, K;) as in the following verse, cited by El-Mufaddal,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waqado Ealima AlA^aqowaAmu A^ano layosa fawoqahu\n                      \n                     \n                        rabN gayoru mano yaEoTiY AlHuZuwZa wayarozuqu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the peoples have known that there is not above him a lord beside Him who gives the portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"of mankind and of others"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and grants the means of subsistence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.) And Ahmad Ibn-Yahyà [i. e. Th] mentions the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA warabiyka laA","text_ar":"لَا وَرَبِيكَ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA warab~ika","text_ar":"لَا وَرَبِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No, by thy Lord, I will not do"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing]; the [latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the reduplication. (M, K: * in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboyika","text_ar":"رَبْيِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["T","IAmb","S","M","A","Msb","K","KL","TA","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}